Overlay patch 0006: let DJUI's auto scale track a 4K drawable on visionOS.

THE BUG (MEASUREMENTS M-15/M-16). On the visionOS simulator the game renders
correctly but the DJUI menu is a narrow strip of unreadable text, while the 3D
scene fills the window. Found by LOOKING at artifacts/vision-sim-03.png, then
traced to a single clamp.

ROOT CAUSE — src/pc/djui/djui_gfx.c:74:

    return clamp(round_to_multiple_f(((f32)windowHeight / (f32)SCREEN_HEIGHT) / 4.0f, 0.5f), 0.5f, 1.5f);

with SCREEN_HEIGHT = 240 (include/config.h:28) and `windowHeight` being the
DRAWABLE height (gfx_sdl.c:288-294 returns the drawable when hidpi is active;
the sim's config has `hidpi true`).

The formula is really "scale = drawableHeight / 960" — a linear DPI scale. The
1.5f ceiling therefore saturates at a 1440-high drawable. Our visionOS drawable
is ~2160 high, because the SDL2 visionOS compat patch deliberately pushes the
drawable to a ~3840 long edge for panel crispness
(SDL_uikitmetalview.m:43-50, Sm64Ios_VisionLongEdge default 3840 — the
VISION-PRO-GUIDE §1.2 fidelity lever). So the drawable keeps growing while the
UI scale stops, and the menu shrinks:

    drawable H | raw scale | clamped | djui multiplier (240/H)*scale
    -----------+-----------+---------+------------------------------
      768      |   0.80    |  1.00   | 0.3125   <- the design reference
     1568      |   1.63    |  1.50   | 0.2296   <- desktop oracle
     2160      |   2.25    |  1.50 * | 0.1667   <- visionOS, SATURATED

THE SMALL MENU IS THE FIDELITY LEVER WORKING, NOT FAILING. The correct fix is
to let the UI scale follow the drawable — NOT to shrink the drawable so the menu
fits, which would trade away the port's single biggest 2D fidelity lever to
paper over a UI-scale bug.

THE FIX: raise the auto-scale ceiling on visionOS only (4.0f tracks a drawable
up to 3840 high, comfortably past our ~2160). At 2160 auto now yields 2.5,
giving a multiplier of 0.2778 — slightly LARGER than the desktop oracle's
0.2296, i.e. comfortably readable.

WHY GATED TO visionOS: a 4K desktop monitor has the same latent saturation, but
changing desktop/iOS behaviour is out of scope and risks regressing a shipping
target. The charter's rule is that the iOS target stays bit-for-bit unaffected.

WHY NOT TOUCH configDjuiScale's 1..4 enum: those are persisted in
sm64config.txt and read by djui_panel_menu_options.c:146's selectionbox
(5 choices) with configfile.c:915 clamping >=5 to 0. Widening the enum would be
a persisted-CVar semantics change needing boot-time migration — precisely the
trap CLAUDE.md flags ("menus that do comboMap.at(storedValue) ABORT on unmapped
legacy values"). Only the auto (0) branch changes here, so every stored value
keeps its exact meaning.

WHY TargetConditionals AND NOT SM64_VISIONOS: SM64_VISIONOS is a CMake variable,
not a compile definition (overlay 0005 adds RAPI_METAL/ENABLE_METAL_BACKEND/
SM64_NO_OPENGL, not SM64_VISIONOS). djui_gfx.c is cross-platform, so the include
is guarded by __APPLE__ to keep Windows/Linux builds untouched. Self-contained in
this patch — no edits inside another patch's hunks (charter D6).

NOT YET VERIFIED ON-SIM: the numbers above are derived, and the exact drawable
height is inferred (3840 long edge / 16:9), not instrumented. This patch must be
validated by a fresh simctl screenshot that is LOOKED AT before it is called
done.

--- a/src/pc/djui/djui_gfx.c
+++ b/src/pc/djui/djui_gfx.c
@@ -11,6 +11,27 @@
 #include "pc/debuglog.h"
 #include "engine/math_util.h"
 
+#ifdef __APPLE__
+#include <TargetConditionals.h>
+#endif
+
+/* Ceiling for DJUI's auto (configDjuiScale == 0) scale.
+ *
+ * The auto formula below is effectively `drawableHeight / 960`, so a ceiling of
+ * 1.5 saturates at a 1440-high drawable. visionOS deliberately renders into a
+ * ~3840-long-edge drawable for panel crispness (see the SDL2 visionOS compat
+ * patch), i.e. ~2160 high, so the stock ceiling would freeze the UI scale while
+ * the drawable kept growing and the menu would shrink to unreadable. 4.0 tracks
+ * up to a 3840-high drawable.
+ *
+ * visionOS-only on purpose: a 4K desktop monitor has the same latent
+ * saturation, but the iOS/desktop targets ship today and are out of scope. */
+#if defined(TARGET_OS_VISION) && TARGET_OS_VISION
+#define DJUI_AUTO_SCALE_MAX 4.0f
+#else
+#define DJUI_AUTO_SCALE_MAX 1.5f
+#endif
+
 const Gfx dl_djui_display_list_begin[] = {
     gsSPTextureAddrDjui(1),
     gsSPEndDisplayList(),
@@ -71,7 +92,7 @@
     if (configDjuiScale == 0) { // auto
         u32 windowWidth, windowHeight;
         gfx_get_dimensions(&windowWidth, &windowHeight);
-        return clamp(round_to_multiple_f(((f32)windowHeight / (f32)SCREEN_HEIGHT) / 4.0f, 0.5f), 0.5f, 1.5f);
+        return clamp(round_to_multiple_f(((f32)windowHeight / (f32)SCREEN_HEIGHT) / 4.0f, 0.5f), 0.5f, DJUI_AUTO_SCALE_MAX);
     } else {
         switch (configDjuiScale) {
             case 1:  return 0.5f;
